title: Worst Keen Fangame
content:
Vorticon World probably, but that game has a "so bad it's good" quality to it. Sort of.

By the way, do we really need to be so critical? It wouldn't be very encouraging to someone thinking of making a fangame if they read all "ALL TEH FANGMAES SUKCS[img]http://www.classicgaming.com/cc314/msgboard/emotikeen-garg.gif[/img] " and such.

P.S. I'm not suggesting that's really what we're saying, just failing to be funny.[img]http://www.classicgaming.com/cc314/msgboard/emotikeen-smile.gif[/img]

P.P.S Also, I really meant "negative" rather than "critical". But, if I must be honest, not many of the fangames I've played were that good...[img]http://www.classicgaming.com/cc314/msgboard/emotikeen-sad.gif[/img] Nothing in particular

content:

title: Re: Worst Keen Fangame
content: Few fangames I've played have really stood out and impressed me, but at the same time I can't say that that many are actually BAD. But Commander Keen: Code Name 13 was bad.  Comically bad.  Absolutely, hilariously, Plan 9 From Outer Space bad.  It was so buggy, so poorly put together, so ridiculous in every way imaginable that it makes me laugh to think about it.  I just hope that the author wasn't really trying.
